Interface ISingleItemQueryModel

All Superinterfaces:
IItemQueryModel, IQueryModel, ISingleQueryModel
All Known Subinterfaces:
IBaseBuildDefinitionQueryModel.IBuildDefinitionQueryModel, IBaseBuildEngineQueryModel.IBuildEngineQueryModel, IBaseBuildResultQueryModel.IBuildResultQueryModel, IBaseCoreDescriptorQueryModel.ICoreDescriptorQueryModel, IBaseFolderDescriptorQueryModel.IFolderDescriptorQueryModel, IBaseReportDescriptorQueryModel.IReportDescriptorQueryModel, IBaseReportQueryDescriptorQueryModel.IReportQueryDescriptorQueryModel, IBaseSharableDescriptorQueryModel.ISharableDescriptorQueryModel, IBaseStorageNodeQueryModel.IStorageNodeQueryModel
public interface ISingleItemQueryModel
extends ISingleQueryModel, IItemQueryModel

Defines the query model for query model roots, or single item references. Instances can be acquired by using the root associated with an item. For example, if an Item subclasses was named Child then the root of the query model could be acquired using ChildQueryModel.ROOT.

Since:
0.5

_eq

IPredicate _eq(IItemHandle handle)
Returns a predicate that evaluates to true when the referenced object is the same object as the specified item.

NOTE: This method should only be used if the value is known at development time. If the value is only known at runtime then input arguments are a more efficient way to construct the query.

Returns:
